        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nWhat is a network resource trying to represent?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "ae6ec946f0505ec7b23081e62f1571cf6d8a6068",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-24 04:39:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nHi Christina,\n\nReferring to https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/AAI-CCVPN+Schema+Proposal+for+Casablanca+Release?preview=/36965962/38114990/AAI-Data-diagram-Topology-2018-Jul-31.png\n\nThe \"network-resource\" is the part labelled as \"zone/tp-network\" from the use case. The relationships are intended to gather up the relationships to the topology (pnf as \"node\", p-interface as \"tp\" and logical-link as \"link\").\n\nThe properties referred to in AAI-1353-10 are derived from an IETF-event-notification.\n\nThanks,\nKeong",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
